               <p>MAJOR SIMPSON. I am <rs id="t18181028-116-viclabel673" type="occupation">clerk</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-116-victim848 t18181028-116-viclabel673"></join> to Mr. Goddard, a sugar-refiner. I missed a shirt out of my chest, and an apron, and found them both on the prisoner. He was wearing them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ARABIN. He said he put them on by mistake. The same person did not wash for us both.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took them by mistake. My washerwoman being ill, I employed the prosecutor's, and she brought them to me as mine.</p>
